WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.080
Hi, my name is Cedric Scherer and I'm excited to be the instructor of the upcoming workshop

00:00:10.080 --> 00:00:14.880
Designing Data Visualizations to Successfully Tell a Story at the Puzzle Conference in Chicago

00:00:14.880 --> 00:00:15.880
this September.

00:00:15.880 --> 00:00:19.760
In this course, you will learn how to create compelling graphics that communicate your

00:00:19.760 --> 00:00:26.719
data in a clear and effective way with a focus on your main insights by guiding and engaging

00:00:26.719 --> 00:00:27.719
the viewer.

00:00:27.719 --> 00:00:31.840
Here are three main reasons why you don't want to miss this workshop.

00:00:31.840 --> 00:00:34.639
Understand the importance of the context in your audience.

00:00:34.639 --> 00:00:39.639
We will cover how to tailor your visualization to your audience and why it's important to

00:00:39.639 --> 00:00:43.320
consider the context in which these visualizations are presented.

00:00:43.320 --> 00:00:48.200
This will hopefully help you to create more effective and engaging graphics in the future

00:00:48.200 --> 00:00:51.119
when communicating your data.

00:00:51.119 --> 00:00:54.599
Learn how to pick a suitable visualization to transport your message.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:59.599
We will discuss the strengths and weaknesses of different chart types and how to pick and

00:00:59.599 --> 00:01:04.919
design a visualization that presents the data in an honest way but with a clear focus on

00:01:04.919 --> 00:01:07.360
your main story.

00:01:07.360 --> 00:01:11.480
Master colors and typefaces when designing data visualizations.

00:01:11.480 --> 00:01:16.680
You will learn how to avoid pitfalls and how to effectively communicate with data by picking

00:01:16.680 --> 00:01:22.800
suitable color palettes and a good combination of colors and fonts to not only transport

00:01:22.800 --> 00:01:26.239
your main message but also the right emotion.

00:01:26.239 --> 00:01:30.839
During the course you will also have the chance to meet like-minded people, exchange about

00:01:30.839 --> 00:01:36.279
your current projects and get feedback on your visualizations thanks to individual and

00:01:36.279 --> 00:01:37.279
group exercises.

00:01:37.279 --> 00:01:41.879
If this sounds interesting to you, then don't miss the chance and join us at the Puzzle

00:01:41.879 --> 00:01:43.239
Conference in Chicago.

